It’s been a minute since I’ve shared my face on my feed and figured it’s a good time to introduce myself! 
I’m Hannah! I married into the MacDonald clan and am proud of it! 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿
A few fun facts about me:
1. I grew up in a tiny Wyoming town… there were 15 kids in my graduating class! And you better believe that at least half of the photos from our Senior slideshow were taken by me 😂 
2. I’m afraid of the dentist. Like… will have a panic attack afraid 🫣 
3. I’m a mom to a very busy boy and girl! Being tired has turned into a personality trait 😂 
4. We live in Mesquite Nevada but most of my clients are from Utah or others traveling to Vegas and Utah! We love living an hour from Vegas and a little over an hour from Zion National Park! 
5. This page started out as a watercolor account. I sold watercolors until I made enough to buy my first camera and lens! The lens I originally bought still spends the most time on my camera! 
If you’re new, be prepared to watch our crazy train 😂 now I have to ask, what brought you to my page?

Did you know all of my destination weddings include a complimentary adventure session? This can include me joining you while you relax on a beachside horseback ride, stand in awe of a scenic hike, or even while you and your lover make-out on a catamaran ride 😉❤️ i LOVE capturing these experiences with my couples and watching their inner romantics and adventurers emerge. What would your ideal adventure session be?

My kids have watched me edits hundreds of times. Today was the first time my little boy hopped on my lap and asked if he could have a go at it. A big part of me wanted to brush him off with a “no I need to get these done.” But I’m happy I listened to the part of me that said “let’s see what he creates!” He was drawn to the colors mostly. He wanted AAALLL the saturation and vibrance and loved the color wheels. My favorite part was when he looked at it with pride in his eyes and said “it’s all done!” It’s a feeling I get when I finish hand editing a photo and feel complete contempt…. It’s when my eyes see nothing that could be added or adjusted that would make the photo better. It’s art. It’s my art. And as my 4 year showed me, it is something we are born with. 💜💙❤️🧡💚

I’m having… feelings over this whole AI photoshop thing.
As a creator I’m absolutely giddy at the endless potential! As a conservationist I love the option to create beautiful scenes without causing destruction. As a photographer I love the options to create insane art!….
But…
As a consumer… will I start questioning what’s real? Will it feed into social medias never ending “unrealistic expectations” race? Will it create more demand from clients who want me to spend more time creating scenes that they never visited? Is it even honest? 

I’m so torn. I’d love to hear your thoughts. 👇

“We’ll just have our friends film it.” 
“We won’t see our video every day like our photos.” 

Guys. Those are the reasons I gave for not getting a videographer. I kick myself every…Single…Time I think about my wedding. My guests were all enjoying themselves (how it should be) and we ended up with only a handful of small videos. It just didn’t do any of the amazing emotions that we felt on our wedding day any justice.
And let’s be honest… it’s 2023…. There are framed TVs. Most homes have some type of screen that rotates videos and photo’s constantly (for us it’s the Amazon Show) Heck! There are even rechargeable wedding albums that play your video on repeat on your coffee table! You most definitely could experience the magic of your wedding every single day ❤️ 

Don’t skimp on the person who is dedicated to eternalizing every emotion on the best day of your life!

Okay. This needs to be said. As we all know, the comment section of ISO photographer posts often end up looking like the seagulls from Finding Nemo 🤦🏼‍♀️ 

Today I saw a iso wedding photographer post where 30/90 comments said “I’d love to be considered ❤️”

No Mikeighlah. If that’s all you have to say you absolutely don’t care if you’re considered or not. No one is going to click on 90 comments. They will scroll through and click on what catches their eye. Your beige marketing strategy will only make someone else stand out more…. Or just overwhelm the poster and they won’t look at anyone’s. This is a free.99 chance to showcase what you’ve got to a hot lead! Don’t bore them before they even see what you have to offer!

I’ve heard this so many times but this is why I take Destination Weddings.
1. I’m a stay at home mom first and foremost. All of my editing work happens when my little ones are asleep. The only time I’m away from them is when I have a shoot or wedding, which I limit so I can have a work life balance. This means I spend 93%-97% of their waking hours with them. 
When I get my kids to bed I go straight to work. I LOVE my job. I’m so passionate about it. But HOLY. It’s exhausting wrestling/playing/cleaning all day and switching to pro mode late into the night. Destination Weddings are a way for me to create while getting a little mom break ❤️ 
2. I have an INCREDIBLE support system. My kids have spectacular grandmas and aunts & uncles who they love visiting…. They usually are disappointed when we get back 😂 
Sometimes I take my kids! My kids are very familiar with car rides and airports. I love sharing my passions and letting them see the world! 
I limit the destination weddings I take. Right now, I’m comfortable only accepting 1-3 a year. While I love traveling, I miss my cute kids way too much to be constantly gone 🥺
Being a mother doesn’t mean the world is over. It doesnt mean you have to disappear and put your dreams into storage. The world actually gets a whole lot bigger! Is it a bit more complicated? And messy? And crazy? Oooh yes 😂 but it also shows you AND them what YOU are capable of, and as a reflection, what THEY are capable of. ❤️❤️❤️

When you book a mother owned photographer, you’re investing in a family.
You’re contributing to the family dinner we have every night. You’re contributing to the sports that will teach my children valuable life lessons.
You’re contributing to a home that keeps my children safe and secure. 
You’re contributing to the power that warms and cools our house. The water we drink. The food we eat. The car we drive. The occasional sanity saving caffeine stop 😂 You’re contributing to a mother who can work and teach her children at home… that is a privilege I don’t take lightly. It’s one that I know is harder and harder for others to maintain. 
YOU make it happen. 
Words don’t begin to cover the gratitude I feel for everyone who has invested in me…. Because you’re not just investing in me… you’re investing in my entire world. 
So you better believe I will always do everything in my power to put my passion and love into your images. They are so much more than pictures to me. And you aren’t just a paycheck to me. You are someone who has so much beauty in your life and are giving me the chance to be with my family, so you’d better believe I want to give you ART that you will love forever. 
For everyone who has booked me, thank you. I have so much love for you. I tear up from gratitude when I think about you. You have helped provide for a family. You know that right? You are the heroes in my story. ❤️ For everyone who WILL book me, my promise is this: Your memories are my priority. If you have a vision, I’ll bring it to life. 

There are some changes coming to Hannah Mac Photography and I’m excited for the elevated experience each of my clients will be receiving. I can’t WAIT to tell your story!

Engagement season is almost upon us! So save these tips to help you plan the perfect surprise or send this to someone who needs it 👀👀👀
 3 tips on planning the perfect proposal. - PART 1.
1. Make sure she looks GOOD. Okay. We know she looks good already but I mean GOOD. All-caps baby. Scheme with a friend who will take her to get her nails done or have a photographer trying to “build their portfolio” reach out to her to see if she wants to model for a styled shoot 👀 don’t let her think that anything was your idea.
2. Have a plan. I’ve dressed up like a hiker, landscape photographer and have even brought other people to photograph to throw your lady off your scent. Know the when & where. Have a script.
3. Take her on dates regularly. If you never do anything special together, it’s going to be a giant red flag if you just randomly decide to take her on a special date… I’m not saying you have to drop a ton of money on dates… but like… star gaze with her, go watch a lightning storm together, feed ducks, go on a hike… you get the picture 📸

Golden Hour traditionally starts about 1 hour prior to sundown. It creates the warmest buttery lighting. 
In the mountains however, golden hour rules are different. You lose the sun A LOT quicker.

Tonight the sunset time was for 7:01 MST in the valley. 
As a rule of thumb, I start 1.5-2 hours before sundown when I shoot in the mountains. We finished our session just after 6:00. Even though it was nearly an hour before sundown in the valley, all of the GOOD light in the mountains was long gone 🥲 I watched photographers who just arrived with their clients walking to a location that *maybe* had 20 minutes of light left. Things that will affect your timing include the height of the mountains and how far away you are from the base. Unless you use off camera lighting, time your sessions in the mountains with care. Don’t trust golden hour 👀

I can’t take full credit for this one 😂 

Recently I scrolled to older posts… I’m talking 2018/2019…. The years before the algorithm started making giant shifts. 
I studied my work and honestly it was frustrating. Each photo got nearly 10x more likes and engagement than now. How is that fair? Since then I’ve invested countless hours trying to improve my trade but THE ALGORITHM was holding me back. It got to the point where I didn’t want to post anymore. What was the point? 

Then I listened to a podcast from @jodymoorecoaching  that hit me. She talked about what the algorithm was for. It’s not created to be this big road block to make some of us fail while others thrive. It’s simply an ever changing system that is always learning and trying to showcase what the viewer wants to see. 
Ah! What a FREEING mindset that is! Now when I post, I’m not racking my brain trying to think about what THE ALGORITHM wants (duhnduhnduhn DUUUUUHN)… that’s impossible. Now, I get to thoughtfully ponder about what YOU want. I get to have fun figuring out how to best connect with beautiful, talented, awesome YOU! You are the people who got me here! My goodness gracious does that make me want to show my creations to you like a proud 5 year old who wants his masterpiece showcased on the fridge for all the world to see! 
So if you’re here, chime in! Did the algorithm bring you here? Were we friends in college, high school, or when I shoved needles into people to get their plasma 💉? If you’re new, welcome to my photography corner of the algorithm! I’ll admit I’m kind of weird (that never changes 😂) but I’m happy you’re here ❤️

Vulnerable Post here.
Social Media often is a place where we see others biggest successes. I think it’s rare that we see the short comings and disappointments that often times feel embarrassing. 
These are some of the images I submitted to the Rocky Mountain Bride cover contest. We hiked nearly 12 miles that day and with every step I was 100% confident this was going to be published. It was an amazing adventure full of bears and blisters. @kaitlin_elise_adventures and her husband were a blast and it was a day that filled a creative hole for me. In my mind, there was no way it WOULDNT be published! 
I waited patiently for the announcement for the National Cover Contest and submitted the photos and story within minutes of it opening. I submitted with full confidence and counted down the days until November 26th… today. This morning I felt surprised when I opened Instagram to see the announced contenders for the magazine cover… and I was not one of them.
Now. This isn’t a pity party. Each and every one of the chosen contenders chosen absolutely deserves to be showcased on the cover. I can’t imagine how difficult of a decision it was to choose. But I still feel disappointed all the same. 
Disappointment stings… but something I’ve learned is that I can wallow and sink into a pit of questioning my work and worth… or… I can thoughtfully evaluate how I can improve for the future. 
This day was amazing whether it was published or not. We got to capture bridals at a bucket list location that very few dare to venture. The couple was adventurous and tough and an absolute blast! They are adventurers and wanted to showcase that through their photos!
 Each contestant who made the contender list absolutely deserves to be there and I’m so excited to see who wins! 
I’ll see you next year @rockymtnbride 😉

Starting a photography business can be fun and exciting… but also confusing and frustrating when you’re trying to find clients. 

Here are the first 3 things I would do if I were to start my business from scratch. 

1. Identify who I want to serve. Seniors? Couples? Families? What do they like to do? Where do they hang out? What do they value and where can I fill their needs and wants?

2. Use insta’s geotag option to find models to build my portfolio. After 8 years in business I STILL do this if I have a concept I want to create and eventually sell. Look at who likes to hang out in the area where you want to shoot and reach out to see if they want photos. The worst they can say is no. Use these portfolio building sessions to build your foundation. 

3. Crunch the numbers. Even if you’re just starting out, you will have business expenses. If you want it to be a part time job, treat it like a part time job. Add your business expenses to your desired yearly revenue then divide it by how many weeks you’d want to work. Use this number to figure out how much you need to make in a week and calculate how many shoots you need to make that happen. It’s okay if you don’t hit your goals at first! But it’s good to know what ball park you should be aiming for ❤️

WE'RE BRINGING A BRIDAL EXPO TO ST GEORGE!!
Two years ago I attended a bridal expo put on by the City of Washington. I ended up booking HALF of my weddings for the year from the wonderful couples I met there! 
However, there were a lot of things about that bridal fair that just missed the spot. I had the pleasure of meeting Kris from @bougieballoonsstgeorge at that event and we both agreed.... Wedding Expos should be hosted by people who live, breathe, and dream about the wedding industry. Period. 
Southern Utah currently issues out over 2000 marriage licenses per year and is predicted to rise with the additional LDS temples along with the rising popularity of Destination Weddings in the National Parks that are in our back yard (Zion, Arches, Moab, Bryce etc) 
Our biggest goal is to connect brides and their families with the best vendors and talent that Southern Utah has to offer! We are limiting the # of each vendor type to ensure that each couple has a diverse amount of options! 
To buy tickets, head over to the link @bougie.bride.fest 
A limited amount of booths are still available to vendors at an early bird discount until February 1st! Each booth purchase includes entrance and a catered meal at a networking event hosted after the expo. 
We are so excited to give this year's couples a one stop shop with the best Southern Utah has to offer!
